1
00:02:49,578 --> 00:02:50,738
I am dead!

2
00:02:51,451 --> 00:02:52,857
I am dead!

3
00:02:53,826 --> 00:02:55,098
I am dead!

4
00:02:55,978 --> 00:02:56,778
Don't hit me!

5
00:02:56,858 --> 00:02:57,938
You won't listen otherwise!

6
00:02:58,018 --> 00:02:59,243
This is your punishment!

7
00:02:59,323 --> 00:03:01,458
I won't make a mistake again, madam!

8
00:03:01,656 --> 00:03:02,508
Don't hit me!

9
00:03:02,588 --> 00:03:03,778
Idiot!

10
00:03:03,905 --> 00:03:06,505
You broke my chandelier
worth 10,000!

11
00:03:06,921 --> 00:03:09,658
Who will pay for the damages?

12
00:03:09,738 --> 00:03:10,768
Answer me!

13
00:03:10,913 --> 00:03:12,458
Secretary!
- Yes madam!

14
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:16,178
Deduct the damage costs every
month from his salary!

15
00:03:16,490 --> 00:03:17,818
But madam!
- But what?

16
00:03:18,098 --> 00:03:20,938
This man has been kept on
a 15 days trial basis!

17
00:03:21,018 --> 00:03:22,618
His salary has not been fixed!

18
00:03:22,698 --> 00:03:25,698
Then fix it, and deduct
the costs from it!

19
00:03:25,778 --> 00:03:28,340
I will fix it and..
- You shut up!

20
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:29,458
Shut up!

21
00:03:30,268 --> 00:03:31,587
Secretary, please keep quiet!

22
00:03:32,058 --> 00:03:34,029
All of you listen carefully!

23
00:03:34,224 --> 00:03:37,554
If anyone makes a mistake,
or does such a damage.

24
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:39,658
Then I will teach him a lesson!

25
00:03:39,898 --> 00:03:41,298
Secretary!
- It hasn't been fixed.

26
00:03:41,378 --> 00:03:42,951
Shut up and follow me!

27
00:03:43,031 --> 00:03:44,298
Definitely! Definitely!

28
00:03:45,818 --> 00:03:49,944
"Heartless,
gave me so much pain.."

29
00:03:50,115 --> 00:03:55,235
"..without knowing
how delicate my heart is.."

30
00:03:55,590 --> 00:04:01,486
"This cruel world.."

31
00:04:10,378 --> 00:04:11,658
Bravo Saigal sir.

32
00:04:11,738 --> 00:04:17,795
"This cruel world.."

33
00:04:23,098 --> 00:04:26,469
I am fed up of your tape.

34
00:04:26,597 --> 00:04:28,218
I am standing here!

35
00:04:28,993 --> 00:04:32,298
You always listen to
such ancient songs.

36
00:04:32,698 --> 00:04:33,658
What has happened to you?

37
00:04:33,738 --> 00:04:35,058
Why didn't you drink this milk?

38
00:04:35,301 --> 00:04:37,218
Milk! What milk?
- This milk!

39
00:04:37,915 --> 00:04:39,138
It was very hot.

40
00:04:39,218 --> 00:04:40,378
So I thought once it cools down..

41
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:42,378
Whether it is hot or cold,
you will have to drink it.

42
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:44,058
Come on, give him the milk.
- Yes madam.

43
00:04:44,698 --> 00:04:47,618
The servants have other work too.

44
00:04:47,698 --> 00:04:51,298
They don't have time to listen
to the tape like you.

45
00:04:51,438 --> 00:04:52,458
Quickly drink the milk.

46
00:04:53,679 --> 00:04:54,898
You have work too.

47
00:04:56,378 --> 00:04:57,458
I stopped drinking milk
in my childhood..

48
00:04:57,538 --> 00:04:58,940
..why are you giving me again?

49
00:04:59,020 --> 00:04:59,982
Madam's orders.

50
00:05:00,062 --> 00:05:01,458
What does your madam care?

51
00:05:01,643 --> 00:05:04,218
First she gives me milk, then
eggs and then thrashes me.

52
00:05:04,863 --> 00:05:06,698
Do one thing, you drink this milk.

53
00:05:07,249 --> 00:05:09,032
Me!
- Yes. - How can I drink this milk?

54
00:05:09,112 --> 00:05:10,578
From your mouth, how else?

55
00:05:10,981 --> 00:05:12,778
Here, keep these pills too.

56
00:05:12,935 --> 00:05:13,618
Drink it.

57
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:15,098
Bravo, drink it.

58
00:05:27,686 --> 00:05:28,618
1!

59
00:05:29,978 --> 00:05:31,058
2!

60
00:06:12,908 --> 00:06:14,098
Brother Suraj!
- Yes!

61
00:06:14,178 --> 00:06:16,778
Why are you gasping?

62
00:06:16,922 --> 00:06:19,298
Nothing, I was just jogging.

63
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:22,898
The neighbour's dog
was scared seeing me.

64
00:06:22,988 --> 00:06:24,810
And so he ran ahead
and I was behind him.

65
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:27,758
So I am gasping.

66
00:06:28,247 --> 00:06:29,098
Okay!

67
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:31,298
So you mean,
you were exercising..

68
00:06:31,378 --> 00:06:33,258
..and the dog came after you.

69
00:06:33,338 --> 00:06:34,532
That's what I am saying.

70
00:06:34,612 --> 00:06:35,618
I am telling the same thing.

71
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:38,178
But are you giving me
morning tea or not?

72
00:06:38,378 --> 00:06:40,018
Why not, surely I will.

73
00:06:40,258 --> 00:06:42,298
But this is a special tea.

74
00:06:42,615 --> 00:06:45,298
Okay, so this is Mr. Vicky's tea.

75
00:06:45,618 --> 00:06:46,778
It is so strange brother.

76
00:06:47,075 --> 00:06:49,178
Until he doesn't drink the
tea prepared by me..

77
00:06:49,258 --> 00:06:50,458
..he doesn't wake up.

78
00:06:50,658 --> 00:06:53,458
He wakes up only listening
to disco and pop music.

79
00:06:53,698 --> 00:06:57,018
But you are fulfilling your duty
by mixing your love in this tea.

80
00:06:58,316 --> 00:07:00,558
But just see that useless,
does he care at all.

81
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:02,508
Heard that!

82
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:03,998
Now he will wake up!

83
00:07:04,318 --> 00:07:04,758
Go!

84
00:07:04,838 --> 00:07:06,696
Fulfill your duty, go.

85
00:07:39,457 --> 00:07:40,462
Vicky!

86
00:07:42,386 --> 00:07:43,478
Vicky!

87
00:07:50,794 --> 00:07:51,734
Aarti you!

88
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:53,218
Why did you switch off the music?

89
00:07:53,344 --> 00:07:55,429
First drink the tea, then
you can dance all you want.

90
00:07:55,566 --> 00:07:57,458
Why do you come to disturb
me every morning?

91
00:07:57,538 --> 00:07:58,466
Why do you bring tea
for me every morning?

92
00:07:58,639 --> 00:08:00,765
Because I like doing things for you.

93
00:08:01,421 --> 00:08:02,816
After all,
we are childhood friends.

94
00:08:02,896 --> 00:08:04,738
Aarti, I am fed up of you!

95
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:07,418
We are no more children,
we have grown up!

96
00:08:07,563 --> 00:08:09,658
The feelings of a person
doesn't change..

97
00:08:09,738 --> 00:08:10,978
..when they grow up.

98
00:08:12,544 --> 00:08:14,298
This girl won't understand.
Keep the tea!

99
00:08:14,738 --> 00:08:15,521
Keep the tea!

100
00:08:15,601 --> 00:08:16,898
Go! Go!

101
00:08:28,323 --> 00:08:30,359
What are you saying Mrs. Poonawala.

102
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:33,098
That's just like darkness
under the lamp.

103
00:08:34,298 --> 00:08:38,218
Just see, you are searching for
a groom for your daughters.

104
00:08:38,298 --> 00:08:40,243
And I am looking for
girls for my son.

105
00:08:40,452 --> 00:08:42,458
And both of us are looking
here and there.

106
00:08:43,298 --> 00:08:45,298
Yes, yes for my son Suraj.

107
00:08:45,778 --> 00:08:46,898
Do one thing.

108
00:08:46,978 --> 00:08:48,698
Come home at 5 o'clock in
the evening for tea..

109
00:08:48,778 --> 00:08:51,018
..along with your daughters.

110
00:08:51,420 --> 00:08:54,018
This way, the children will
see each other too.

111
00:08:55,037 --> 00:08:57,538
Okay then, see you
at 5 o'clock. Bye.

112
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:00,258
May I come in madam?
- Come in.

113
00:09:01,878 --> 00:09:04,398
Good morning madam.
- Good morning.

114
00:09:04,688 --> 00:09:08,608
Secretary, today at 5 o'clock my
best friend is coming for tea.

115
00:09:08,781 --> 00:09:09,778
Along with her daughters.

116
00:09:10,018 --> 00:09:11,260
To fix the alliance.

117
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:14,258
Be ready and..
- It's very nice of you madam.

118
00:09:14,414 --> 00:09:16,458
There are very few women
like you in our country.

119
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:20,458
5 years after my wife died,
you thought about me.

120
00:09:20,538 --> 00:09:22,778
Shut up you fool!
- Why shut up madam.

121
00:09:22,858 --> 00:09:25,778
They are coming for Suraj.
- Oh! My fault! I am sorry!

122
00:09:25,858 --> 00:09:26,785
Secretary.
- Yes.

123
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:30,378
Cancel all the appointments
that are in the afternoon!

124
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:31,722
How is that possible madam?

125
00:09:31,802 --> 00:09:33,818
Today afternoon you have
to go to the widow home..

126
00:09:33,898 --> 00:09:37,088
Secretary, do as I say!
- Yes.

127
00:09:37,220 --> 00:09:39,618
Because today's tea party
is more important for me.

128
00:09:39,698 --> 00:09:41,874
No arguments go home and make
all the arrangements.

129
00:09:41,954 --> 00:09:42,938
Diary closed.

130
00:09:43,058 --> 00:09:44,578
Come, come.

131
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:45,538
Come.

132
00:09:49,121 --> 00:09:50,678
Miscreant, fell asleep standing.

133
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:53,798
There is always a party
in this house.

134
00:09:54,278 --> 00:09:58,298
But today's party is very
important for madam.

135
00:09:58,439 --> 00:10:01,537
Her son's alliance is
about to be fixed.

136
00:10:01,618 --> 00:10:04,205
None of you should make a mistake.

137
00:10:04,285 --> 00:10:06,153
If anyone of you makes a mistake..

138
00:10:06,233 --> 00:10:08,779
..then I will be court-marshaled
along with you..

139
00:10:08,859 --> 00:10:10,696
Secretary!
- Madam, good morning.

140
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:12,637
Good afternoon!
- Oh, good afternoon.

141
00:10:12,717 --> 00:10:14,762
Have you explained them properly?

142
00:10:14,842 --> 00:10:15,727
I was just doing that, madam.

143
00:10:15,807 --> 00:10:18,058
If anyone makes a mistake.

144
00:10:18,318 --> 00:10:22,503
Then I will flog him,
where is your uniform.

145
00:10:22,684 --> 00:10:23,949
Madam, my child urinated on it.

146
00:10:24,046 --> 00:10:27,559
Shut up!
Go and change your uniform!

147
00:10:27,658 --> 00:10:28,978
Secretary, explain him!

148
00:10:29,058 --> 00:10:30,138
I will explain him, madam.

149
00:10:30,218 --> 00:10:32,498
Stupid, quickly go and
change your uniform.

150
00:10:32,578 --> 00:10:34,778
Or else, you will also
do what your child did.

151
00:10:34,971 --> 00:10:35,978
Correct.

152
00:10:37,924 --> 00:10:39,698
Greetings mummy.
- What is this nonsense?

153
00:10:39,978 --> 00:10:42,458
Even the servants of this
house speak English.

154
00:10:42,538 --> 00:10:47,537
And even after doing M.A, you are
still stuck up in ancient era.

155
00:10:47,874 --> 00:10:49,938
Greetings mother! Greetings father!

156
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:51,178
What is all this?

157
00:10:51,532 --> 00:10:55,229
Look, if you want to live
in today's society..

158
00:10:55,309 --> 00:10:57,258
..then learn its etiquette too!

159
00:10:57,709 --> 00:10:59,498
And what are you wearing?

160
00:10:59,778 --> 00:11:04,338
I want to see you well dressed,
up to date, but..

161
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,178
Mummy, a man's character is
reflected from his behaviour..

162
00:11:07,298 --> 00:11:09,338
..and not his clothes.

163
00:11:09,891 --> 00:11:13,641
Wow! What great thoughts.

164
00:11:13,858 --> 00:11:16,618
Instead of taking birth in this
family, you should have..

165
00:11:16,698 --> 00:11:18,978
Been born in a respected family.

166
00:11:19,693 --> 00:11:21,319
Mr. Bhandari.
- Yes.

167
00:11:21,456 --> 00:11:26,247
When I am talking to my son,
please don't interfere!

168
00:11:26,327 --> 00:11:28,030
I know that he is your son..

169
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:31,658
..but co-incidentally I am his
father too. - Keep quiet!

170
00:11:31,738 --> 00:11:33,858
I have been quiet right
from my marriage.

171
00:11:34,168 --> 00:11:35,187
What was I saying?

172
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:36,418
I don't know.

173
00:11:36,825 --> 00:11:39,498
I was saying, Suraj today
evening Mr. Poonawala..

174
00:11:39,578 --> 00:11:42,898
..is coming for tea along
with her three daughters.

175
00:11:43,476 --> 00:11:44,178
Really!

176
00:11:44,547 --> 00:11:45,840
But why?

177
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:49,967
Because she is searching for
a groom for her daughters.

178
00:11:50,069 --> 00:11:52,509
So, will he marry all
those three girls?

179
00:11:52,639 --> 00:11:55,589
Mr. Bhandari again you..
- Good afternoon everybody.

180
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:57,252
Hi! Hi mom!

181
00:11:57,332 --> 00:11:58,029
Hi dad!

182
00:11:58,589 --> 00:11:59,669
Hi brother, how are you?

183
00:12:00,232 --> 00:12:02,116
You are looking so
smart and handsome!

184
00:12:02,196 --> 00:12:03,210
Where are you going?

185
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,060
There is a tennis match
in the college.

186
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:07,453
I am getting late, mom.
- Wish you all the best! - See you.

187
00:12:07,701 --> 00:12:08,469
Bye.

188
00:12:08,660 --> 00:12:09,669
By dad.
- Bye.

189
00:12:10,789 --> 00:12:12,229
Did you see your younger brother?

190
00:12:12,429 --> 00:12:14,561
He is so smart and mod.
- A lot.

191
00:12:14,641 --> 00:12:16,798
I had dreamt the same
things about you, but..

192
00:12:16,878 --> 00:12:19,868
Yes, the dreams she had seen
for me, those are shattered.

193
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:21,229
Now she wants to make
you the scapegoat.

194
00:12:21,309 --> 00:12:23,207
Mr. Bhandari, I told you..
- I am sorry.

195
00:12:23,483 --> 00:12:24,589
Suraj!
- There.

196
00:12:24,949 --> 00:12:26,509
Please keep quiet!
- Alright.

197
00:12:26,845 --> 00:12:29,069
Suraj, guests are arriving
in the evening.

198
00:12:29,218 --> 00:12:31,069
Before that, you will
come in my room.

199
00:12:31,429 --> 00:12:34,589
Because I will select
your dress, understood.

200
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:37,029
Mummy, I will..
- No arguments, that's all!

201
00:12:39,844 --> 00:12:41,749
Father..
- No arguments.

202
00:12:41,867 --> 00:12:43,778
There is no place for arguments
in this government.

203
00:12:43,858 --> 00:12:44,749
Didn't you hear? Go!

204
00:12:44,988 --> 00:12:46,229
This government has to change.

205
00:12:46,309 --> 00:12:47,629
First you change you clothes.

206
00:12:52,389 --> 00:12:53,549
Gopi.
- Yes madam.

207
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:55,749
I am getting Suraj ready.

208
00:12:56,149 --> 00:12:59,349
Inform me as soon as Mr. and
Mrs. Poonawala arrive.

209
00:12:59,466 --> 00:13:00,309
Go.

210
00:13:01,837 --> 00:13:02,989
No good.

211
00:13:03,069 --> 00:13:06,389
O yes! This is the colour.

212
00:13:06,789 --> 00:13:09,829
Wear this Suraj you will
look very cute in this.

213
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:11,309
What a beautiful colour!

214
00:13:11,809 --> 00:13:12,509
Mummy.
- I like this.

215
00:13:12,669 --> 00:13:14,829
Mummy, you are treating
me like a child.

216
00:13:14,909 --> 00:13:16,909
Can't I..
- Will you keep quiet?

217
00:13:17,391 --> 00:13:18,829
Do as I say!

218
00:13:18,999 --> 00:13:20,069
They will be arriving.

219
00:13:20,207 --> 00:13:21,869
Come on wear this, no arguments.

220
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:23,509
Thank you.

221
00:13:24,299 --> 00:13:26,389
Come, come Mrs. Chunawala.

222
00:13:26,804 --> 00:13:28,909
Oh no Mr. Bhandari.

223
00:13:29,069 --> 00:13:31,229
How many times have I told you!

224
00:13:31,309 --> 00:13:33,909
I am Mrs. Poonawala
and not Chunawala.

225
00:13:33,989 --> 00:13:38,642
It is so, rose called by any
other name is still rose.

226
00:13:38,751 --> 00:13:40,057
It won't turn into a cauliflower.

227
00:13:40,137 --> 00:13:40,881
What?

228
00:13:40,976 --> 00:13:42,244
I didn't understand what you meant!

229
00:13:42,604 --> 00:13:46,509
You will not understand,
your husband would have.

230
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:49,149
I say, your husband is so fortunate.

231
00:13:49,421 --> 00:13:52,469
He got such a lovely wife like you.

232
00:13:53,709 --> 00:13:55,061
You are married.

233
00:13:55,141 --> 00:13:59,149
But you don't look like you are
a mother of three children.

234
00:14:00,149 --> 00:14:01,829
Thank you very much
for the compliment.

235
00:14:01,909 --> 00:14:03,244
You have maintained
your figure so well.

236
00:14:03,324 --> 00:14:04,149
So nice.

237
00:14:04,229 --> 00:14:05,989
Tell the secret to my wife too.

238
00:14:06,069 --> 00:14:07,858
Her waistline is increasing.

239
00:14:07,938 --> 00:14:09,069
Mr. Bhandari.

240
00:14:09,749 --> 00:14:11,709
Come, come you have
a very long life.

241
00:14:11,789 --> 00:14:13,029
We were just talking about you.

242
00:14:13,245 --> 00:14:15,109
There is a call for you, please go.

243
00:14:15,249 --> 00:14:18,509
No, there is always a call
for me at such occasions.

244
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:21,749
Forgive me Mrs. Chuanawala..
Kathawala!

245
00:14:21,829 --> 00:14:24,469
No, no Tambakuwala..
- Poonawala.

246
00:14:24,549 --> 00:14:25,427
What difference does it make?

247
00:14:25,507 --> 00:14:27,923
Rose flower, cauliflower,
did it make any difference.

248
00:14:28,003 --> 00:14:30,429
Mr. Bhandari!
- Yes, I am leaving.

249
00:14:32,183 --> 00:14:37,303
Mrs. Bhandari, your husband
is so interesting.

250
00:14:37,383 --> 00:14:41,090
He talks so well, how sweet of him.

251
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:43,429
Mrs. Poonawala, Thank you very much.

252
00:14:43,583 --> 00:14:46,824
This is my son, Suraj Bhandari, M.A.

253
00:14:47,486 --> 00:14:49,029
Greetings aunt.
- Greetings.

254
00:14:49,429 --> 00:14:51,509
Son, these are my daughters.

255
00:14:51,996 --> 00:14:53,069
Anita.
- Hi.

256
00:14:53,331 --> 00:14:54,909
And she is Vanita.
- Hello.

257
00:14:55,029 --> 00:14:57,429
And this is Sunita.
- Hi.

